Variation.
The male paratypes are very similar in overall size (SVL 
57.7–76.3 mm
) and head proportion (HW/ SVL 0.41–0.47, HL/SVL 0.44–0.50) to the holotype. The females are smaller (SVL 
52.5–59.4 mm
) and have shorter and narrower heads (HW/SVL 0.38–0.40; HL/SVL HL/SVL 0.39–0.43) (
Fig. 9
